<TITLE> 30 hurt in BCL clash at Rangpur Medical College </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Rangpur, Dec 13 (bdnews24.com)  At least 30 students were injured as clashes erupted between two factions of Chhatra League at Rangpur Medical College on Sunday. Seven critically injured were admitted to the medical college hospital. Rangpur thana police officer Abdur Rashid told bdnews24.com that activists loyal to two different Chhatra League leaders fought over establishing supremacy on campus. The violence began around midnight on Saturday, and continued into the early hours of Sunday, he said. The rioting students vandalised about 20 rooms of three hostels, he said. Additional police were deployed on the campus. College principal Dr Azizul Islam said: "The motives behind the violence are being investigated." Rangpur Awami League leaders held a meeting at around midday with the Chhatra League activists "to resolve the situation". After the meeting, Rangpur AL joint convener Rezaul Karim Razu told bdnews24.com: "We asked them the reason of the violence and warned both groups against further such incidents." bdnew
